<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-451-539  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 451 539.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>LAN Times  Sept 1990 v7 n9 p239(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Microsoft meets its nemesis? (WordPerfect Corp tackles officeautomation) (company profile)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Burns, Nina.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>WordPerfect Corp, having defeated Microsoft Corp in themicrocomputer word processing arena, is now pioneering the localarea network (LAN)-based office automation market.andP;  WordPerfectCorp, founded in 1979, experienced growth of 58 percent in 1989,to $218 million, and 1990 sales are expected to exceed $400million.andP;  Second qtr 1990 results were up 68 percent over the samequarter in 1989, totalling $106.3 million.andP;  WordPerfect, thecompany's flagship product, ranks first in the world in sales ofword processors, holding 63 percent of the US market and 40percent worldwide.andP;  To this is added WordPerfect Office, an officeand business automation package geared to the network environment.andO;It has three components: Office PC is a standalone product withCalendar, File Manager, Calculator, Editor, Notebook, RepeatPerformance, Shell, and TSR Manager; Office LAN adds electronicmail and scheduling for single-server LANs; Office Connectionscontributes store-and-forward, distribution, and gateway servicesbetween multiple Office hosts and to other mail systems.andO;WordPerfect has developed its own enterprise-messaging platform.andO;Such systems comprise the message transport engine, the mailapplication, and mail-enabled applications.andP;  If WordPerfectsucceeds in all its plans for WordPerfect Office, it will be aleader in the next wave of software companies and applications.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   WordPerfect Corp. (earnings).andO;Product:   WordPerfect (Word processing software) (sales statistics)WordPerfect Office (Office automation software) (design andconstruction).andO;Topic:     Company ProfileOffice AutomationOffice Automation SoftwareLocal Area NetworksSoftware PublishersProfitGrowth.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>